 Re: I almost feel sorry for this girl</span><hr size=1> I am NOT a parrent becasue of a diliberate choice on my part, and extreme caution before, durring, and regarding sex.  This is why I will not sit here and tell other parrents they are good or bad, since I don't honestly know.<br>
HOWEVER, being in my 30s, many of my friends ARE parents.  Their kids call me their uncle, and they look up to me like a big brother.  It is a nice feeling, and though I do enjoy their affection, I do NOT want to be a parent.  People who do it earn my respect for their efforts (including you, Maus) and I will be the first to say that you are doing something I do NOT want to do and have taken measures to avoid.<br>
HOWEVER....<br>
I also know what kids are like (having been one myself) and I know it is damn stupid to think that you will say NO, however forcefully, and think it is now law.  If the kid TRULY wants the god damn cookie, (s)he will GET the god damn cookie, MARK MY WORDS.  Some of my friends are in their early 40s, and trust me, when your daughter gets to be in her mid teens, if you even know where in the hell she REALLY IS half the time, you are doing VERY well.<br>
Don't fool yourself into thinking you rule your household with an iron fist.  I have watched parents make this mistake, then get devastated when their little Jimmy ends up in jail for car-jacking.  Your daughter is 6 years old, Maus.  You have another 10 years of peace.  Ignore me if you want to, it's YOUR daughter, and I DON'T WANT ONE.<br>
In my opinion, kids are great, providing you can preserve your sanity and marriage long enough to get them out of the house.<br>
I'm not saying that the parents were or were not to blame.  Yes, I saw that you stated that they should SHARE the blame, which may or may NOT be true.  As I stated before (get that baseball cap out of your eyes), YOU DON'T KNOW!  Perhaps the parents were TOTALY to blame, or maybe they did all they could.  Maybe they were so scared of EXACTLY this happening that they nearly choked her to death with restrictions, so she waited for a single opportunity to get away, and DID.  Maybe they never watched, then were shocked to look for her one day, and realize she was gone.  Or, maybe they dared her to take off, then were only mildly surprised when she did.  This is only a few of MILLIONS of possibilities, NOBODY knows.  The only thing we do know is that when soldier-boy saw the report in Germany, he put her on a plane back home (though not right away, and the only thing I have heard is that he was scared and confused).  If you want to say you blame the parents for it, FINE, do that.  If anything, I say she was DAMN FUCKING LUCKY if the worst thing she had to deal with was stale peanuts and jet lag.  Furthermore, I will also say that if these parents leave that computer where she can use it without their CLOSE supervision, they are fucking idiots.  They are lucky this worked out as well as it did this time.  If it were to happen again, they may not get as lucky.  If it happened again, THEN I would say they are to blame, but I won't make that assumption this time until I know more about them AND her.<br>
