<br>
I won't disagree that some kids are born with a tendency to do bad things.  How the parents handle it has a direct bearing on just how bad that kid turns out to be.<br>
<br>
If that were my kid, and they knew beforehand that meeting a older man online was wrong, lying about their age was wrong, and leaving the country without me knowing it was wrong (if this was my kid they would know AND they would know the consequences of their actions beforehand) and they still did this then I'd turn them over to the PINS program.  <br>
<br>
Here in NYS that is Person In Need of Supervision.  It's a 24/7 supervised living environment where the kids are forced to be accountable for what they do and if that fails and they still elect to get into trouble they go on to reform school.<br>
<br>
Tough love sucks but if that's the only option you take it, or you risk having a child do as this one did.  Thankfully she made it home safely and has another chance.  Most do not.<br>
<br>
As a parent I'll tell you flat out, you move heaven and earth to get through to your kids and if that fails then it IS your fault if you don't take corrective measures.  <br>
<br>
